projects.description:
The main subject of the assignment is to support the implementation of three urban transport initiatives 
announced in the White Paper “Towards a single European Transport Area”. The three initiatives are:
Initiative 31: Urban Mobility Plans;
Initiative 32: EU framework for urban road user charging and access restriction schemes;
Initiative 33: A strategy for ‘near zero-emission urban logistics’ by 2030.
client: European Commission, DG Move

Development of a Dutch knowledge portal targeted at local authorities and event organisers on preparing, organising and managing transport and mobility of large, medium and small events.

Tasks: preparing guidelines on several event mobility topics; 
Client: CROW, the Dutch knowledge centre on transport and mobility
